It can be ruled out that the police captain of the XXII district, who killed a pedestrian on Tuesday and resigned in the meantime, would be driving under the influence of alcohol or narcotics, Attila Morvai, a spokesman for the Attorney General’s Office of the capital, said on Friday after an expert assessment of the case was finalized.
