What insurance is suitable for me?
Car insurance, which protects the driver in the event of an accident. represents a significant expense, which depends on various factors such as age, status, gender, length of possession of a driving licence, the type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured person.
This obligation takes the form of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the insurance company will receive the agreed insurance amount in a certain amount for taking charge of the payment of damages in the event of an insured event.
Insurance premium is the price of insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors such as age, status, gender, length of possession of a driving licence, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the more likely an accident is, the higher the premium rate.
For this reason, both people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of checks, insurance companies concluded that married people have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of travel and thus the likelihood of having an accident.
As the number of trips increases, the likelihood increases.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when setting the price of insurance premiums.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the insurance that best fits his profile of the insured.
We will show here the most important variables for choosing this or that type of insurance, which, in addition to satisfying the type of insured, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of twenty-five face various disadvantages such as little driving experience and a short driving license when they want to arrange insurance premiums at an affordable price.
Although insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks with a discounted premium so as to get insurance coverage for all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would involve the client’s participation in the payment of the insured event.
"The part of the premium payment provided by the client will be predetermined in determining the premium price, which will be the higher, the lower the contribution," explains Luis Noguera, Chief Executive Officer of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other traffic participants so that the client insures against damage caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, it would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
Recommendations.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be attentive and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce your insurance premiums in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the insurance company has.
In contrast, malus is an increase in the aforementioned base rate.
"Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus,” Noguera explains.
After crossing the twenty-five-year limit, it is easier for drivers when they go to arrange insurance, as their client's risk index decreases, thanks to the experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to arrange insurance against all risks at a discount.
"Young people are usually unable to take advantage of the experience they have gained in advance when an accident occurs, or even when driving," the director of a European company in Spain assures, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of the procedure, when the "newcomer's fear" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but has no children, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows it.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies to be the clients with the lowest risk index and therefore their surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with a premium discount (which could be 300 euros) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other road users, starting from the third year from the purchase of the vehicle.
"Their driving is calmer and their purchasing power is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount," says Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are recommended insurance against all risks with a premium discount (up to <0xE2><0x82><0xAC> 150) or insurance extended to other participants in the operation, if a high bonus has been achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is a good reason to properly study the insurance options that would suit us best in our personal situation.
