Mr. Black also fears that the Scottish NHS does not have an accurate idea of the amount of foreign personnel it employs.
But his report stressed that the other key checks went well on a sample of five health authorities.
The President of the Supreme Audit Office was interested in personnel from countries outside the European Economic Area immediately after the June attacks on Glasgow Airport.
Bilal Abdullah, a 28-year-old Iraqi doctor at the Royal Alexandra Hospital in Paisley, was detained at the airport after a Jeep crashed into the door of the main terminal building.
