The survey also found that the established inspection procedures at the NHS authorities in the areas of Ayrshire and Arran, Grampian, Greater Glasgow and Clyde, Lanarkshire and Lothian are being largely implemented.
They included passport, work permit and qualification checks.
The Scottish government is currently revising the policies and directives of pre-employment controls for NHS foreign workers.
Health Secretary Nicola Sturgeon said: “I wanted to get this job done immediately after the terrorist attack at Glasgow Airport.”
She also added that the Scottish government, in consultation with the health commissions, will consider the recommendations of this report and ensure that best practices appear in the updated pre-employee inspection directives for all staff – including foreign ones – that it plans to issue next month.
