Two months ago, when the prime minister avoided calling an election and insulted the British intelligentsia by claiming that this decision was not influenced by polls, there was hope that he would secure a resilient and effective government.
Instead, as the increasingly humorous Liberal Democrat deputy chairman put it, the once feared Mr. Brown changed from Stalin to Mr. Bean.
